data.description: New price plus a Seller paid $17,000 concession for a 2-1 Interest Rate Buydown for a 2% interest rate reduction in year one & a 1% interest rate reduction in year two of Buyer's Loanoffered on this charming home in the Millwood golf course community. Spectacular French Quarter, New Orleans-style architecture, and so much character inside and out! The homefeatures approximately 4,891 square feet of living space, with 4 bedrooms, 2 full and 3 half baths, multiple living areas, and a finished area over the 3-car garage that would make either a wonderful home office, guest quarters, or man cave. The welcoming front porch & foyer withbuilt-in cabinetry & open railing leads to a large living room with a beautiful cast stone fireplace, crown molding, and 100-year-old reclaimed hardwood floors. The open-concept living & dining area with lots of windows & natural light joins the recently updated kitchen with painted &stained cabinetry, quartz countertops, newer stainless appliances, and a spacious island. The main level also boasts a handy mud/laundry room and a simply spectacular master suite with ahotel-quality, spa-like master bath and a HUGE walk-in closet! The fully finished basement offersthree additional bedrooms, 1.5 baths, a large family room with a brick & stone wall, secondfireplace, and a wet bar with refrigerator and dishwasher, making entertaining a breeze! For outdoor enjoyment, your family will love the large, private backyard & courtyards surroundedby trees and lush landscaping. Feel like you are vacationing year-round in this lovely home with optional country club amenities available through millwoodgolf.com. Call today for your private showing!
